<h1 class="name">Nicholas Burkard</h1>
<p class="tagline">Technical Art Lead &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Generative 3D Pipelines &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; OpenUSD</p>
<p class="contact">mercuryghoest@gmail.com</p>
<hr class="rule" />

<h2>Professional Experience</h2>

<div class="job">
  <div class="job-header">
    <span class="job-title">Technical Art Lead</span>
    <span class="job-meta">02/2022 &ndash; Present</span>
  </div>
  <div class="company-line"><span class="company">Meta</span> &middot; Remote</div>
  <p>Technical Art Lead for generative AI 3D pipelines including characters, animation, and environments for Horizon. Responsible for prototyping, building, and refining data sets for state-of-the-art generative 3D model texture and rigging models. Built plans with XFN partners across technical and non-technical fields to define roadmaps, staff teams, create demos, and work with teams training models &mdash; from training through shipping surfaces &mdash; ensuring products succeed and fulfill user expectations.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Built pipelines spanning Gaussian splat characters and traditional polygon characters running on Meta's cloud infrastructure, and deployed C++ code across the Family of Apps (Facebook, WhatsApp, Instagram).</li>
    <li>Architectural lead and <span class="accent">first inventor of the patented Avatar content pipeline</span> &mdash; a dynamic parametric avatar character pipeline built on OpenUSD, delivering avatar content for <span class="accent">billions of users</span> across many platforms.</li>
    <li>Led backend design of <em>Artcastle</em>, an OpenUSD-based cloud content storage solution tracking USD and character-choice dependencies across Meta Avatars, Fantastical Avatars, Codec Avatars, and Instagram Pets.</li>
    <li>Responsible for open-sourcing <em>Noodles</em>, Meta's high-performance node-graph graphics library, and <em>usdNoodles</em>, an upcoming addition to Pixar's OpenUSD open-source library.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="job">
  <div class="job-header">
    <span class="job-title">Head of Technical Animation</span>
    <span class="job-meta">02/2013 &ndash; 02/2022</span>
  </div>
  <div class="company-line"><span class="company">Walt Disney Animation Studios</span> &middot; Burbank, CA</div>
  <ul>
    <li>Head of Technical Animation on <em>Encanto</em>; Technical Animation Supervisor on <em>Zootopia</em> and <em>Wreck-It Ralph 2</em>; TechAnim Artist on <em>Moana</em> and <em>Frozen</em>.</li>
    <li>Led a team of <span class="accent">40+ tech artists</span> across films, simulating hair and cloth shots and translating 2D art direction into simulated final frames.</li>
    <li>Built out pipelines including the latest OpenUSD WDAS pipeline and tooling to support production at scale.</li>
    <li>Part of the team responsible for porting Pixar's <em>Presto</em> animation software to Disney Animation.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="job">
  <div class="job-header">
    <span class="job-title">CFX Artist</span>
